parameters: Kru "Umi... I heard from the chief... You can't leave the forest, can you?"
Umi "Just thinking about it... makes my legs tremble..."
Umi "If Umi hadn't been so selfish... Toto would be..."
Umi "It's Umi's fault... Umi is to blame for what happened to Toto..."

Kru "I understand that Umi is blaming herself... I know you're carrying a
lot of pain."
Kru "I also understand how important your father and mother were to you..."

Kru "But... even so, there are many other things that are important to Umi
now."
Kru "I know that you feel you have to protect them..."
Umi "I think Umi has to do something about it."

Kru "Despite going through such tough times, you're trying to persevere and
overcome them."

Umi "Umi is weak... but the reason I think about becoming stronger is
because of Mia..."

Umi "Yes. Ever since Toto and Kaka disappeared, Umi couldn't speak at
all... It was very troubling..."

Umi "Then, when I was in the forest, I met Mia who was a kitten at the
time. Mia was very weak... and I thought I had to do something, and from
there, I somehow found strength..."

Umi "After that, Umi was able to speak again... and became energetic in
order to raise Mia."
Kru "I see... The Umi now exists thanks to Mia, huh."

Umi "Yes... If it weren't for Mia, Umi would have remained sad forever.
Thanks to Mia, I became cheerful... and because of that, many things became
fun."

Umi "Like chatting with everyone in the village, playing with Mia, eating
meat, and also with you..."
Umi "Mmm... It's nothing. Anyway... even though it's scary..."
Umi "...I'm going to get that herb."
Umi "If I'm with you... I feel like I can do my best."
Kru "It'll definitely be okay! I'm with you! Let's go!"
At that moment, the girl smiled...

In front of a harsh trial that must be overcome, she smiled as she took a
trembling step forward...
It was the moment when the girl became a little more grown-up...
It was the moment when a person becomes a little stronger...
Thump... A sound echoed deep in my heart...
"Head towards Tamagawa Mountain. Tamagawa Mountain is located west of the\nvillage, keep going straight."
Kru "Alright! Let's set off for Tamagawa Mountain!"
Kru: "I don't want to go ahead and fall again, so I'll stop here."
Shall we return to the village?
